<dec f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/widgets/qsplitter.h' l='53' type='QList&lt;int&gt; QSplitter::sizes() const'/>
<def f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/widgets/qsplitter.cpp' l='1560' ll='1574' type='QList&lt;int&gt; QSplitter::sizes() const'/>
<doc f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/widgets/qsplitter.cpp' l='1544'>/*!
    Returns a list of the size parameters of all the widgets in this splitter.

    If the splitter&apos;s orientation is horizontal, the list contains the
    widgets width in pixels, from left to right; if the orientation is
    vertical, the list contains the widgets&apos; heights in pixels,
    from top to bottom.

    Giving the values to another splitter&apos;s setSizes() function will
    produce a splitter with the same layout as this one.

    Note that invisible widgets have a size of 0.

    \sa setSizes()
*/</doc>
